]]: Maj Arthur J. Hawhe, Ltc Joseph H. Thornton\n* [[69th Regiment Indiana Infantry|69th Indiana]]: Col [[Thomas W. Bennett (territorial governor)|Thomas W. Bennett]], Ltc Oran Perry\n* [[7th Regiment Kentucky Volunteer Infantry|7th Kentucky]]: Ltc John Lucas, Col [[Reuben May]]\n* [[120th Ohio Infantry|120th Ohio]]: Col [[Marcus M. Spiegel]]\n|-\n| 2nd Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol Daniel W. Lindsey\n|\n* [[54th Indiana Infantry Regiment|54th Indiana]]: Col Fielding Mansfield\n* [[22nd Regiment Kentucky Volunteer Infantry|22nd Kentucky]]: Ltc George W. Monroe\n* [[16th Ohio Infantry|16th Ohio]]: Cpt Eli W. Botsford, Maj Milton Mills\n* [[42nd Ohio Infantry|42nd Ohio]]: Ltc [[Don A. Pardee]], Col [[Lionel Allen Sheldon|Lionel A. Sheldon]]\n* [[114th Ohio Infantry|114th Ohio]]: Col [[John Cradlebaugh]], Ltc John H. Kelly\n|-\n| Cavalry\n|\n* [[2nd Regiment Illinois Volunteer Cavalry|2nd Illinois Cavalry]] (5 companies): Ltc Daniel B. Bush, Jr.\n* [[3rd Regiment Illinois Volunteer Cavalry|3rd Illinois Cavalry]] (3 companies): Cpt John L. Campbell\n* [[6th Missouri Volunteer Cavalry|6th Missouri Cavalry]] (7 companies): Col Clark Wright\n|-\n| Artillery\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCpt Jacob T. Foster\n|\n* 7th Battery, Michigan Light: Cpt Charles H. Lanphere\n* [[1st Independent Battery Wisconsin Light Artillery|1st Battery, Wisconsin Light]]: Lt Oscar F. Nutting\n|-\n| rowspan=3 |\nTenth Division\n\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Andrew J. Smith]]\n<br>\n\n\nEscort\n* 4th Indiana Cavalry, Company C: Cpt Andrew P. Gallagher\n| 1st Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Stephen G. Burbridge]]\n|\n* [[16th Regiment Indiana Infantry (3 years)|16th Indiana]]: Col Thomas J. Lucas, Maj James H. Redfield\n* [[60th Indiana Infantry Regiment|60th Indiana]]: Col Richard Owen\n* [[67th Regiment Indiana Infantry|67th Indiana]]: Ltc Theodore E. Buehler\n* [[83rd Ohio Infantry|83rd Ohio]]: Col Frederick W. Moore\n* [[96th Ohio Infantry|96th Ohio]]: Col Joseph W. Vance\n* [[23rd Wisconsin Volunteer Infantr