 Illinois Volunteer Infantry Regiment|108th Illinois]]: Ltc Charles Turner\n* [[120th Illinois Volunteer Infantry Regiment|120th Illinois]]: Col George W. McKeaig\n* [[131st Illinois Volunteer Infantry Regiment|131st Illinois]]: Col George W. Neeley, Maj Joseph L. Purvis\n* [[10th Illinois Volunteer Cavalry Regiment|10th Illinois Cavalry]], Companies A, D, G, and K: Maj Elvis P. Shaw\n|-\n| African Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Isaac F. Shephard]]\n|\n* [[8th Louisiana Regiment Infantry (African Descent)|8th Louisiana]]: Col [[Hiram Scofield]] (also commanded Post of Milliken's Bend, La)\n* [[9th Louisiana Regiment Infantry (African Descent)|9th Louisiana]]: Col [[Hermann Lieb]], Maj Erastus N. Owen, Ltc Charles L. Page\n* [[11th Louisiana Regiment Infantry (African Descent)|11th Louisiana]]: Col Edwin W. Chamberlain, Ltc Cyrus Sears\n* [[13th Louisiana Regiment Infantry (African Descent)|13th Louisiana]]: Lt H. Knoll\n* [[51st United States Colored Infantry Regiment|1st Mississippi]]: Ltc A. Watson Webber\n* [[53rd United States Colored Infantry Regiment|3rd Mississippi]]: Col Richard H. Ballinger\n|-\n| Post of Goodrich's Landing, La.\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol William F. Wood\n|\n* [[1st Arkansas Infantry Regiment (Union)|1st Arkansas]]: Ltc James W. Campbell\n* [[10th Louisiana Regiment Infantry (African Descent)|10th Louisiana]]: Ltc Frederick M. Crandall\n|}\n\n<br />\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n==References==\n*U.S. War Department, [http://cdl.library.cornell.edu/moa/browse.monographs/waro.html ''The War of the Rebellion'']: ''a Compilation of the [[Official Records of the American Civil War|Official Records]] of the Union and Confederate Armies'', U.S. Government Printing Office, 1880&ndash;1901.\n*U.S. War Department, ''The War of the Rebellion: a Compilation of the Official Records of the Union and Confederate Armies'', U.S. Government Printing Office, 1880&ndash;1901:  [http://ebooks.library.cornell.edu/cgi/t/text/pageviewer-idx?c=moawar&cc=