pt Frederick Sparrestrom\n* Battery G, 2nd Illinois Light:<ref>By the collision of two steamers May 1, 1863, near Grand Gulf, MISS., this battery lost all its guns, and was sent to Memphis to refit. It rejoined the army at Vicksburg June 30. Meantime Captain Sparrestrom had been assigned, June 16, to the command of Battery D, First Illinois Light Artillery.</ref> Cpt Frederick Sparrestrom, Lt John W. Lowell\n* [[Battery \"L\", 2nd Regiment Illinois Volunteer Light Artillery|Battery L, 2nd Illinois Light]]: Cpt William H. Bolton\n* 8th Battery, Michigan Light: Cpt Samuel De Golyer, Lt Theodore W. Lockwood\n* [[3rd Ohio Battery|3rd Battery, Ohio Light]]: Cpt William S. Williams\n|-\n| rowspan=4 |\nSixth Division\n\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[John McArthur]]\n<br>\n\n\nEscort\n* [[11th Illinois Volunteer Cavalry Regiment|11th Illinois Cavalry, Company G]]: Lt Stephen S. Tripp\n| 1st Brigade<br>(Post of Lake Providence)\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Hugh T. Reid]]\n|\n* [[1st Regiment Kansas Volunteer Infantry|1st Kansas]]: Col William Y. Roberts\n* [[16th Wisconsin Volunteer Infantry Regiment|16th Wisconsin]]: Col [[Benjamin Allen (Wisconsin politician)|Benjamin Allen]]\n|-\n| 2nd Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Thomas E.G. Ransom]]\n|\n* [[11th Illinois Volunteer Infantry Regiment|11th Illinois]]: Ltc Garrett Nevins, Ltc James H. Coates\n* [[72nd Illinois Volunteer Infantry Regiment|72nd Illinois]]: Col [[Frederick Augustus Starring|Frederick A. Starring]]\n* [[95th Illinois Volunteer Infantry Regiment|95th Illinois]]: Col Thomas W. Humphrey, Ltc Leander Blanden, Col Thomas W. Humphrey\n* [[14th Wisconsin Volunteer Infantry Regiment|14th Wisconsin]]: Col [[Lyman M. Ward]]\n* [[17th Wisconsin Volunteer Infantry Regiment|17th Wisconsin]]: Ltc Thomas McMahon, Col Adam G. Malloy\n|-\n| 3rd Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol William Hall\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Alexander Chambers]]<ref>Assumed command June 6.</ref>\n|\n* [[11th Iowa Volunteer Infantry Regiment|11th Iowa]]: 