telli.html|archivedate=January 6, 2009|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"ln-funk-third ear\">{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=RIEjkWXZdrMC&pg=PA164#v=onepage&q&f=false|title=Funk, Third Ear: The Essential Listening Companion|author=Dave Thompson|publisher=Hal Leonard|year=2001|accessdate=October 10, 2017|isbn=9780879306298|pages=164\u2013169}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"ln-gibson-2010\">{{cite web|url=http://www.gibson.com/news-lifestyle/features/en-us/leo-nocentelli-0716.aspx|title=The Gibson Interview \u2013 Leo Nocentelli of The Meters|author=Bryan Wawzenek|publisher=Gibson.com|date=July 16, 2010|accessdate=October 10, 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160515121831/http://www.gibson.com/news-lifestyle/features/en-us/leo-nocentelli-0716.aspx|archivedate=May 15, 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"ln-nola2015perform\">{{cite web|url=http://www.nola.com/jazzfest/index.ssf/2014/11/the_meter_men_featuring_phishs.html|title=The Meter Men, featuring Phish's Page McConnell, to headline Joy Theater during 2015 New Orleans Jazz Fest|author=Keith Spera|publisher=nola.com|date=November 10, 2014|accessdate=October 10, 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150531194124/http://www.nola.com/jazzfest/index.ssf/2014/11/the_meter_men_featuring_phishs.html|archivedate=May 31, 2015|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"ln-gratefulweb-2015\">{{cite web|url=http://www.gratefulweb.com/articles/grateful-web-interview-leo-nocentelli|title=Grateful Web Interview with Leo Nocentelli|author=Dylan Muhlberg|publisher=gratefulweb.com|date=May 11, 2015|accessdate=October 10, 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170925012110/http://www.gratefulweb.com/articles/grateful-web-interview-leo-nocentelli|archivedate=September 25, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"ln-nola-aug2011\">{{cite web|url=http://www.nola.com/voodoofest/index.ssf/2011/08/latest_meters_reunion_to_roll.html|title=Latest Meters reunion to roll on at least through Voodoo 