oboyu, zi mnoyu, i hodi (\u0417 \u0442\u043e\u0431\u043e\u044e, \u0437\u0456 \u043c\u043d\u043e\u044e, \u0456 \u0433\u043e\u0434\u0456)\"\n| \u2014 || \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Chudova Myt\u02b9 (\u0427\u0443\u0434\u043e\u0432\u0430 \u041c\u0438\u0442\u044c)\"\n| \u2014 || \u2014\n|Non-album single\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Ty (\u0422\u044b)\"\n| rowspan=\"9\" | 2019\n| \u2014 || \u2014\n| rowspan=\"5\" |''<small>Octopus</small>''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Oh, No!\"\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Expectations\" \n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Your Entertainment\"\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Want You To Stay\"\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20190320190758/http://www.melovin.com.ua/ M\u00c9LOVIN Official Website] (english)\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{S-ach}}\n{{Succession box\n| before = Dmitry Babak\n| title = [[X-Factor (Ukrainian TV series)|X-Factor Ukraine]]<br />Winner\n| years = 2015\n| after = [[Sevak Khanagyan]]\n}}\n{{Succession box\n| before = [[O.Torvald]]<br>with \"[[Time (O.Torvald song)|Time]]\"\n| title = [[Ukraine in the Eurovision Song Contest]]\n| years = [[Eurovision Song Contest 2018|2018]]\n| after = [[Go_A]]<br>with \"[[Solovey (song)|Solovey]]\"<small>(\u0421\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0439)</small>\n}}\n{{S-end}}\n{{Ukraine in the Eurovision Song Contest}}\n{{Eurovision Song Contest 2018}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Melovin}}\n[[Category:1997 births]]\n[[Category:English-language singers from Ukraine]]\n[[Category:Eurovision Song Contest entrants of 2018]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Odessa]]\n[[Category:Ukrainian electronic musicians]]\n[[Category:Ukrainian Eurovision Song Contest entrants]]\n[[Category:Ukrainian male singers]]\n[[Category:Ukrainian pop singers]]\n[[Category:Ukrainian songwriters]]\n[[Category:The X Factor winners]]\n[[Category:Ukrainian people of Russian descent]]\n[[Category:21st-century Ukrainian singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century male singers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2018}}\n{{short description|Ukrainian singer and songwriter}}\n{{Eastern Slavic name|Mykolayovych|Bocharov}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = M\u00e9lovin\n| image            = [[File:Melovin.jpg|thumb|\u0447\u0435\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0435\u043a \u0432 \u043e\u0447\u043a\u0430\u0445 \u043d\u0430 \u0444\u043e\u0442\u043e]]\n| caption          = M\u00e9lovin at the Eurovision Song Contest 2018.\n| image_size       = 250px\n| background       = solo_singer\n| alias            = \n| birth_name       = Kostyantyn Mykolayovych Bocharov\n| birth_date       = {{birth date and age|1997|4|11|df=yes}}\n| birth_place      = [[Odesa]], [[Ukraine]]\n| death_date       = \n| death_place      = \n| origin           = \n| instrument       = {{Hlist|Vocals, Piano}}\n| genre            = {{flatlist| \n* [[Electropop]]\n* [[Dark pop]]\n* [[Pop rock]]\n}}\n| occupation       = {{hlist|Singer|songwriter}}\n| years_active     = 2015\u2013present\n| label            = \n| associated_acts  = \n| website          = {{url|melovinmusic.com}}\n| Girlfriend:      = @helga_official_\n}}\n'''Kostyantyn Mykolayovych Bocharov''' ({{lang-uk|\u041a\u043e\u0441\u0442\u044f\u043d\u0442\u0438\u0301\u043d \u041c\u0438\u043a\u043e\u043b\u0430\u0301\u0439\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447 \u0411\u043e\u0447\u0430\u0440\u043e\u0301\u0432}}; born 11 April 1997), better known by his stage name '''M\u00e9lovin (\u041c\u0435\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0456\u043d)''' (stylised as '''M\u00c9LOVIN'''), is a [[Ukraine|Ukrainian]] singer and songwriter. He first came to prominence after winning season six of ''[[X-Factor (Ukrainian TV series)|X-Factor Ukraine]]''.\n\nHe [[Ukraine in the Eurovision Song Contest 2018|represented Ukraine]] in the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2018]] in [[Lisbon]], [[Portugal]], with the song \"[[Under the Ladder]]\", finishing in seventeenth place, with 130 points. \n\n==Early life==\nBocharov was born in [[Odesa]] to parents Mykola Bocharov and Valentyna Bocharova. He became interested in music at a young age, and as a child would put on and perform in concerts at his school.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://musicstarts.com.ua/eksklyuziv-pobeditel-shou-x-faktor-6-kostya-bocharov-otkrovenno-o-svoix-uvlecheniyax-uchebe-vospitanii-i-zhelanii-stat-artistom/|title=\u041f\u043e\u0431\u0435\u0434\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c \u0448\u043e\u0443 \"\u0425-\u0444\u0430\u043a\u0442\u043e\u0440-6\" \u041a\u043e\u0441\u0442\u044f \u0411\u043e\u0447\u0430\u0440\u043e\u0432 \u043e\u0442\u043a\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e \u043e \u0441\u0432\u043e\u0438\u0445 \u0443\u0432\u043b\u0435\u0447\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f\u0445, \u0443\u0447\u0435\u0431\u0435, \u0432\u043e\u0441\u043f\u0438\u0442\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0438 \u0438 \u0436\u0435\u043b\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0438 \u0441\u0442\u0430\u0442\u044c \u0430\u0440\u0442\u0438\u0441\u0442\u043e\u043c|date=6 January 2016|website=musicstarts.com.ua|language=Russian}}</ref> He later began attending a music school, but left before graduating. He subsequently enrolled in a theatre school, which he graduated from.<ref name=STB>{{cite web |url=http://fakty.ua/210707-pobeditel-h-faktora-konstantin-bocharov-kogda-nazvali-moe-imya-nogi-u-menya-podkosilis-i-ya-upal-pryamo-na-scene|title=\u041f\u043e\u0431\u0435\u0434\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c \"\u0425-\u0444\u0430\u043a\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0430\" \u041a\u043e\u043d\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043d\u0442\u0438\u043d \u0411\u043e\u0447\u0430\u0440\u043e\u0432: \"\u041a\u043e\u0433\u0434\u0430 \u043d\u0430\u0437\u0432\u0430\u043b\u0438 \u043c\u043e\u0435 \u0438\u043c\u044f, \u043d\u043e\u0433\u0438 \u043f\u043e\u0434\u043a\u043e\u0441\u0438\u043b\u0438\u0441\u044c, \u0438 \u044f \u0443\u043f\u0430\u043b \u043f\u0440\u044f\u043c\u043e \u043d\u0430 \u0441\u0446\u0435\u043d\u0435\"|first=Taisiya|last=Bakhareva|date=30 December 2015|website=fakty.ua|language=Russian}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n===2015\u20132016: ''X-Factor Ukraine''===\nBocharov had auditioned for ''[[X-Factor (Ukrainian TV series)|X-Factor Ukraine]]'' three times, but never got onto the televised show.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.048.ua/news/1052181|title=\u041e\u0434\u0435\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0442 \u041a\u043e\u0441\u0442\u044f \u0411\u043e\u0447\u0430\u0440\u043e\u0432: \u041f\u043e\u0439\u0442\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \"\u0425-\u0444\u0430\u043a\u0442\u043e\u0440\" \u043c\u0435\u043d\u044f \u0432\u0434\u043e\u0445\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u043b\u0430 \u043f\u043e\u043a\u043e\u0439\u043d\u0430\u044f \u0431\u0430\u0431\u0443\u0448\u043a\u0430|author=Olga|date=6 December 2015|language=Russian}}</ref> Eventually, he passed his audition for the show's sixth season in 2015.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mig.com.ua/novosti/item/12398-kh-faktor-6-igor-kondratyuk-o-pobede-kosti-bocharova|title=\"\u0425-\u0424\u0430\u043a\u0442\u043e\u0440-6\": \u0418\u0433\u043e\u0440\u044c \u041a\u043e\u043d\u0434\u0440\u0430\u0442\u044e\u043a \u2013 \u043e \u043f\u043e\u0431\u0435\u0434\u0435 \u041a\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438 \u0411\u043e\u0447\u0430\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0430|website=mig.com.ua|accessdate=19 February 2018|language=Russian}}</ref> He advanced through the competition and was eventually declared the winner. Following the show's completion, he went on a tour of Ukraine along with the show's other finalists.<ref name=STB/> In 2016, he released his debut single \"Ne odinokaya\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/ru/album/%D0%BD%D0%B5-%D0%BE%D0%B4%D0%B8%D0%BD%D0%BE%D0%BA%D0%B0%D1%8F-single/1100401940?l=en|title=\u041d\u0435 \u043e\u0434\u0438\u043d\u043e\u043a\u0430\u044f \u2013 Single \u2013 M\u00c9LOVIN|website=itunes.apple.com|accessdate=19 February 2018}}</ref>\n\n===2017\u2013present: Eurovision attempts and new song(s)===\nOn 17 January 2017, Bocharov was announced as one of the 23 competitors in ''[[Ukraine in the Eurovision Song Contest 2017|Vidbir 2017]]'', the Ukrainian national selection for the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2017]], with the song \"Wonder\".<ref>{{cite web|title=\u041e\u043f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0435\u043b\u0435\u043d\u044b \u0438\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0430 \u043f\u043e\u043b\u0443\u0444\u0438\u043d\u0430\u043b\u0438\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0432 \u041d\u0430\u0446\u0438\u043e\u043d\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u043e\u0442\u0431\u043e\u0440\u0430 \u043d\u0430 \u00ab\u0415\u0432\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435-2017\u00bb|url=http://eurovision.stb.ua/ru/2017/01/17/opredeleny-imena-polufinalistov-natsionalnogo-otbora-na-evrovidenie-2017/|website=stb.ua|publisher=[[STB (TV channel)|STB]]|accessdate=17 January 2017|language=Ukrainian|date=17 January 2017}}</ref> Bocharov competed in the third semi-final on 18 February 2017, where he placed second and qualified to the final as one of the top two finishers.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://eurovoix.com/2017/01/20/ukraine-semi-finals-running-order-announced/|title=Ukraine: Semi Finals Running Order Announced|publisher=Eurovoix|date=20 January 2017|last=Granger|first=Anthony}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://eurovoix.com/2017/02/19/ukraine-vidbir-semi-final-three-results/|title=Ukraine: Vidbir Semi-Final Three Results|date=19 February 2017|publisher=Eurovoix|last=Halliwell|first=Jamie}}</ref> In the semi-final, he received the highest number of televotes from the Ukrainian public but only placed fourth with the jury consisting of [[Konstantin Meladze]], [[Jamala]], and [[Verka Serduchka|Andriy Danylko]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://esctoday.com/141243/ukraine-final-line-national-selection-complete/|title=Ukraine: Final line-up of national selection complete|date=18 February 2017|publisher=ESCToday|last=Weaver|first=Jessica}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=\u0421\u0442\u0430\u043b\u043e \u0432\u0456\u0434\u043e\u043c\u043e \u0456\u043c\u2019\u044f \u0434\u0440\u0443\u0433\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0447\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0430 \u0436\u0443\u0440\u0456 \u043d\u0430\u0446\u0432\u0456\u0434\u0431\u043e\u0440\u0443 \u00ab\u0404\u0432\u0440\u043e\u0431\u0430\u0447\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044f-2017\u00bb|url=http://eurovision.stb.ua/ua/2016/09/13/stalo-izvestno-imya-vtorogo-chlena-zhyuri-natsotbora-evrovidenie-2017/|website=stb.ua|publisher=[[STB (TV channel)|STB]]|accessdate=13 September 2016|language=Ukrainian|date=13 September 2016}}</ref> The final was held on 25 February 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://esctoday.com/141522/ukraine-will-follow-jamalas-footsteps-6-acts-contention/|title=Ukraine: Who will follow Jamala\u2019s footsteps ? 6 acts in contention|publisher=ESCToday|last=Jiandani|first=Sanjay|date=23 February 2017}}</ref> Bocharov placed third, after receiving the highest number of televotes from the Ukrainian public again, but placing second-to-last with the jury.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://esctoday.com/141662/ukraine-o-torvald-represent-host-nation-eurovision-2017/|title=Ukraine: O.Torvald to represent the host nation at Eurovision 2017!|last=Weaver|first=Jessica|date=25 February 2017|publisher=ESCToday}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://eurovoix.com/2017/02/25/ukraine-o-torvald-represent-host-country-kyiv/|title=Ukraine: O.Torvald to represent the host country in Kyiv|date=25 February 2017|publisher=Eurovoix|last=Halliwell|first=Jamie}}</ref>\n\n[[File:M\u00e9lovinUnderTheLadder.ogg|thumb|Ukrainian singer M\u00e9lovin singing a cappella his 2018 Eurovision entry Under The Ladder.]]\n[[File:M\u00e9lovingreetingsrussian.ogg|thumb|Ukrainian singer M\u00e9lovin sends regards at the Eurovision Song Contest 2018.]]\n[[File:M\u00e9lovininterview.ogg|thumb|Chat with the Ukrainian singer M\u00e9lovin during the Eurovision Song Contest 2018.]]\n\nThe following year, Bocharov confirmed his return to ''Vidbir'' on 16 January 2018 after being confirmed as one of the 18 competing acts in ''[[Ukraine in the Eurovision Song Contest 2018|Vidbir 2018]]'' with the song \"[[Under the Ladder]]\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://eurovoix.com/2018/01/16/ukraine-vidbir-2018-contestants-revealed/|title=Ukraine: Vidbir 2018 Contestants Revealed|date=16 January 2018|publisher=Eurovoix|last=Farren|first=Neil}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://esctoday.com/156489/ukraine-uapbc-reveals-national-selection-participants/|title=Ukraine: UA:PBC reveals national selection participants|date=16 January 2018|publisher=ESCToday|last=Jiandani|first=Sanjay}}</ref> He competed in the second semi-final on 17 February 2018, where he qualified to the final as one of the top three finishers, placing first with the highest number of televotes from the Ukrainian public and second-highest number of jury votes from the jury consisting of [[Jamala]], [[Verka Serduchka|Danylko]], and [[Onuka (band)|Eugene Filatov]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://eurovoix.com/2018/01/19/ukraine-vidbir-2018-semi-finals-order/|title=Ukraine: Vidbir 2018 Semi-Finals Running Order Revealed|date=19 January 2018|publisher=Eurovoix|last=Herbert|first=Emily}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://eurovoix.com/2018/02/17/ukraine-vidbir-2018-finalists-selected/|title=Ukraine: Vidbir 2018 Finalists Selected|date=17 February 2018|publisher=Eurovoix|last=Granger|first=Anthony}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://esctoday.com/156611/ukraine-vidbir-2018-semi-final-running-order-draw-results/|title=Ukraine: Vidbir 2018 semi-final running order draw results|last=Knoops|first=Roy|date=19 January 2018|publisher=ESCToday}}</ref><ref name=\"sf2\">{{cite web|url=http://esctoday.com/159508/ukraine-vidbir-2018-final-lineup-completed/|title=Ukraine: Vidbir 2018 Final lineup completed|date=17 February 2018|publisher=ESCToday|last=Vranis|first=Michalis}}</ref> He won the final on 24 February and thus represented Ukraine in the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2018]] in [[Lisbon]], [[Portugal]].<ref name=\"sf2\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://esctoday.com/159742/ukraine-melovin-will-fly-lisbon/|title=Ukraine: Melovin will fly to Lisbon!|last=Jiandani|first=Sergio|date=24 February 2018}}</ref> He placed 17th in the voting in [[Eurovision Song Contest 2018]] final, gaining only eleven points from juries of 43 countries and 119 points from televiewers all around the world. After Eurovision 2018, he went on to release his new single \"That's your role,\" which has had many views on Youtube.\n\n==Discography==\n===Extended plays===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:14em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:16em;\"| Details\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''Face to Face''\n| \n* Released: 10 November 2017\n* Label: [[Universal Music Publishing Group|UMPG]]\n* Format: Digital download, CD\n|}\n\n===Singles===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:16em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:1em;\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"2\"| Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Album\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"| UKR\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Sverigetopplistan|SWE<br>Heat.]]<br><ref name=\"SWE\">{{cite web|url=http://www.sverigetopplistan.se/netdata/ghl002.mbr/lista?liid=215&dfom=20180511|title=Veckolista Heatseeker \u2013 Vecka 20, 18 maj 2018|publisher=[[Sverigetopplistan]]|accessdate=18 May 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Ne odinokaya (\u041d\u0435 \u043e\u0434\u0438\u043d\u043e\u043a\u0430\u044f)\"\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 2016\n| \u2014 || \u2014\n| rowspan=\"2\" {{n/a|Non-album singles}} \n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Na vzlyot (\u041d\u0430 \u0432\u0437\u043b\u0451\u0442)\"\n| \u2014 || \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Wonder\"\n| \u2014 || \u2014\n| rowspan=\"6\" |''Face to Face''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Unbroken\"\n| rowspan=\"5\" | 2017\n| \u2014 || \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Hooligan\"\n| \u2014 || \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Play This Life\"\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Face to Face\"\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Svit v poloni\"\n(\u04